1ï¸âƒ£ Traditional JavaScript vs. React
Before React, developers used vanilla JavaScript or jQuery to manipulate the DOM manually.
ğŸ”´ Problem: When the app grew bigger, it became slow, messy, and hard to maintain.

âœ… React solves this problem by:
âœ” Making UI component-based (Reusable UI parts)
âœ” Using a Virtual DOM (Fast updates without affecting the real DOM)
âœ” Providing a unidirectional data flow (Predictable UI behavior)
âœ” Supporting React Hooks (Easier state management)

